# Use shadcn/ui only

All UI in this project is built with **shadcn/ui** components (Radix + Tailwind v4,
neutral base color). This is a hard requirement.

## Rules

- Build UI from shadcn/ui primitives in `components/ui/*` (`Button`, `Card`,
  `Badge`, `Table`, `Tabs`, `Sidebar`, `Separator`, etc.). Add new ones with
  `npx shadcn@latest add <component>`.
- Do **not** introduce another component library or hand-rolled CSS classes for
  new UI. Prefer Tailwind utility classes + shadcn variants over the legacy
  custom classes in `styles/*.css`.
- Compose class names with the `cn()` helper from `@/lib/utils`.
- Use design tokens (`bg-background`, `text-foreground`, `text-muted-foreground`,
  `border`, `bg-card`, `bg-primary`) — never hardcode hex colors in components.
- Icons come from `lucide-react`.
- Legacy views styled with `styles/workspace.css` / `styles/features.css` are
  being migrated to shadcn incrementally; when you touch one, convert it.

## Example

```tsx
import { Card, CardContent, CardHeader, CardTitle } from "@/components/ui/card";
import { Badge } from "@/components/ui/badge";

<Card>
  <CardHeader><CardTitle>Monthly revenue</CardTitle></CardHeader>
  <CardContent>
    <div className="text-3xl font-bold">$189,540</div>
    <Badge variant="secondary">+27.9%</Badge>
  </CardContent>
</Card>
```
